Gen Z turned job hopping into office frogging — the new corporate buzzword no one asked for. Forget “climbing the ladder,” workers are leaping like frogs across jobs (and maybe relationships). Are you an office frog, a job hugger, or just stuck in the pond? We roast the trend, the stigma, and why loyalty doesn’t pay anymore. Warning: mass layoffs may now be called “corporate croaking.”
title: Office Frogging: The Dumbest Corporate Trend Yet
